-- Center Vincent Lecavalier Reaches Agreement With NHL Flyers
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-07-03T04:01:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-03/center-vincent-lecavalier-reaches-agreement-with-nhl-flyers.html
CenterVincent Lecavalier agreed to a
multiyear contract with the  Philadelphia Flyers , the National
Hockey League team said.  The Flyers declined to disclose terms of the agreement,
which ESPN said is worth $22.5 million over five years and
contains a no-movement clause.  Lecavalier, 33, has spent 14 seasons in the NHL, all with
the  Tampa Bay  Lightning, where he has posted 383 goals and 491
assists for 874 points in 1,037 regular-season games. The
Lightning bought out the final seven years of his contract for
$32.67 million to be paid during the next 14 years, NHL.com
reported.  Lecavalier also has 52 points in 63 playoff games,
including nine goals and 16 points to help lead the Lightning to
the Stanley Cup championship in 2004.  This past season with Tampa Bay, Lecavalier had 10 goals
and 22 assists for 32 points, while appearing in his 1,000th NHL
game on Jan. 21 at the  New York Islanders .  Lecavalier was the No. 1 overall pick in the 1998 NHL Entry
Draft.  To contact the reporter on this story:
